636. an fratris...] ‘or was it that thou mightest behold thy brother’s cruel death ?‘ The force of an is pathetic. It is often used in rhetorical argument to introduce a question an affirmative answer to which is almost impossible (eg. ‘ This must be true. Or will you argue that ‘2²3 cf. Cic. Cat. l. 1. 3), but here the point is that the answer which might have been supposed impossible is the true one. She must have been sent to witness her brother-'s death.
